ul tests of spring-boot-actuator 3.0.0 core APIs; the javac failure is due to Spring Boot 3 API changes from 2.6.x.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Spring Boot 3.0 removed or renamed several 2.6-era Actuator APIs, including HttpTrace in favor of HttpExchange-style APIs, and changed constructors such as HealthEndpoint, EnvironmentEndpoint, and Sanitizer.\",\n    \"Some Actuator integration health indicators depend on optional third-party clients; tests should avoid those optional integration packages unless they intentionally add the corresponding dependency.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04d2153700966968016a428b8ac9488197a55ab2c450d28f5d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1221, "output": 874, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21551, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782745982159, "responseId": "resp_04d2153700966968016a428b7e9a1081978d7a29a7dbfc81ad"}}
